MDXXXVI.

TRANSLATION OF A FINAL OONOORD WHEREBY ROGER WILLIAMs REOOVERS AGAINST THOMAS GRIFFITH AND ELIZABETH HIS WIFE LANDS IN YSTRADYVODUGK.

11 APRIL. 8 WILL. III. 1696.

This is the final agreement made in the court of the Lord the King of his great session of the eounty of GLAMORGAN held at CARDIFF in the oounty aforesaid on Saturday the eleventh day of April in the eighth year of the reign of the Lord WILLIAM the Third after the Gonquest King of ENGLAND SCOTLAND FRANCE and IRELAND Defender of the Faith &a Before WILmAM PowLETT Serjeant-at-law and EDWARD SMYTH esquire justioes and other faithful people of the Lord the King then there present Between ROGER WILL1AMs gentleman plaintiff and THOMAs GRIFFITH gentleman and ELIZABETH his wife deforciants of one messuage one barn one garden ten aeres of land thirty aeres of meadow twenty aeres of pasture and a hundred and twenty aeres of furze and heath with appurtenanoes in the parish of YSTRADYVODUCK whereof a plea of oovenant was summoned between them in the same court to wit that the aforesaid THOMAs and ELIZABETH aeknowledged the tenements aforesaid with appurtenanees to be the right of the same ROGER as those which the same Roemz has of the gift of the aforesaid THOMAS and ELIZABETH And those they have remised and quitolaimed for themselves and the heirs of the same THOMAs to the aforenamed ROGER and his heirs for ever And moreover the same THOMAS and ELIZABETH have granted for themselves and the heirs of the same THOMAS that they will warrant the tenements aforesaid with appurtenanees to the aforenamed Ros-ER and his heirs against all men for ever And for this aoknowledgment remise quitolaim warrant fine and agreement the same Roomz has given to the aforenamed

THOMAs and ELIZABETH a hundred and sixty pounds sterling.
